<br><br>
I chose these two becuase the Frodo is the best for general use and the Ring is good as I need Sting exertions.<br>
<br><br>
Bid nothing, this deck doesn&#39;t have to get out anything specific first turn, but if you can, do. (Hobbiton Party Field, Farmer Maggot&#39;s Fields, Green Dragon Inn, The Prancing Pony).<br>
<br><br>
As for the other companions, you may notice I tagged three as starting. If you go second and your opponent plays Green Dragon Inn, start Legolas and Gimli. Otherwise, start Legolas and Sam. However, if your opponent starts Shire Lookout Point, you could try starting Gandalf (Pony is very popular in my metagame so I&#39;ve never seen this).<br>
<br><br>
Adventure Deck<br>
<br><br>
Let&#39;s see: Pony for Aragorn, Ettenmoors for the pump, Courtyard for the denial, Stairway for the damage, Bridge because I have to, Dale because this is Moria, Wilderland for the NO ARCHERY, Shores for the twilight and stop, Summit for the cards.<br>
<br><br>
Free Peoples<br>
<br><br>
Companions: Gimli for the denial, Legolas for the fighting, Gandalf for the cards, Aragorn for more denial, Boromir for the pump, Merry for more pump, Pippin for the removal and Sam for more denial.<br>
<br><br>
Allies: Elrond for the cards and Bilbo for the recycling.<br>
<br><br>
Weapons: Pretty much every unique strength-boosting weapon for every companion.<br>
<br><br>
Support: Only in Gondor and Shire, those two are the big groups.<br>
<br><br>
Gandalf&#39;s Cart: Yes, three.<br>
<br><br>
Shadow:<br>
<br><br>
This is Moria stompy, not swarm. If someone could tell me how to change this to swarm or archery with minimal rares needed, much appreciated, d-mail me. Yes, having the bakcup common Balrog has helped me.<br>
<br><br>
Anyway, this is my last deck before TTT, then there&#39;ll be changes galore.<br>
<br><br>
Thanks.    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
